    <p><strong>The quantum threat is not theoretical — it is a present governance challenge.</strong> Nation-state
    adversaries are actively collecting encrypted traffic today for decryption once cryptographically relevant
    quantum computers (CRQCs) become available. NIST predicts the first post-quantum certificates won't be
    commercially available until 2026, while CNSA 2.0 requires pure post-quantum algorithms in U.S. national
    security systems by 2035. PQC software vendors need ISO 42001's PDCA loop <em>now</em>, not at deployment.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-primary); margin: 32px 0 16px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase;">NIST PQC STANDARDS — ISO 42001 GOVERNANCE MAPPING</h3>

  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">FIPS 203 · Primary KEM</div>
      <div class="algo-name">ML-KEM</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">Module-Lattice Key Encapsulation<br>(ex. CRYSTALS-Kyber)</div>
      <div class="algo-purpose">Primary standard for general encryption and secure key exchange. Comparatively small key sizes, high operational speed. Targeted for broad adoption across TLS, SSH, and PKI infrastructure.</div>
      <div class="algo-42001">
        <strong>ISO 42001 Governance Touch</strong>
        Clause 8.2: Risk assess AI components selecting ML-KEM parameter sets (512/768/1024). Clause 8.4: Impact assess systemic risk of ML-KEM adoption failures in dependent services.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">FIPS 204 · Primary DSA</div>
      <div class="algo-name">ML-DSA</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">Module-Lattice Digital Signature<br>(ex. CRYSTALS-Dilithium)</div>
      <div class="algo-purpose">Primary standard for protecting digital signatures. Used in code signing, certificate issuance, and document authentication. AI-automated signing pipelines require AIMS governance.</div>
      <div class="algo-42001">
        <strong>ISO 42001 Governance Touch</strong>
        Clause 6.1.4: Impact assessment for AI-automated signing decisions. Annex A.7.1: Audit log requirements for repudiation prevention in AI-assisted signature workflows.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">FIPS 205 · Backup DSA</div>
      <div class="algo-name">SLH-DSA</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">Stateless Hash-Based Signature<br>(ex. SPHINCS+)</div>
      <div class="algo-purpose">Backup signature method using different mathematical foundations than ML-DSA. Intended to provide diversity — if ML-DSA proves vulnerable, SLH-DSA provides algorithmic continuity.</div>
      <div class="algo-42001">
        <strong>ISO 42001 Governance Touch</strong>
        Clause 6.3: Planning of changes — governance of fallback triggers from ML-DSA to SLH-DSA. Clause 10: Corrective action protocols for algorithm deprecation events.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">FIPS 203 Backup · Mar 2025</div>
      <div class="algo-name">HQC</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">Hamming Quasi-Cyclic<br>Code-Based Scheme</div>
      <div class="algo-purpose">Fifth NIST PQC algorithm, announced March 2025 as backup for ML-KEM using code-based (not lattice) mathematics. Draft FIPS expected early 2026, final ~2027. Provides mathematical diversity.</div>
      <div class="algo-42001">
        <strong>ISO 42001 Governance Touch</strong>
        Clause 10: Continuous improvement — AIMS must incorporate HQC readiness into the improvement cycle. Clause 4.1: Update organisational context as HQC standard evolves through 2027.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">SP 800-208 · Specialised</div>
      <div class="algo-name">LMS / XMSS</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">Stateful Hash-Based Signatures<br>Hardware &amp; Gov. Use</div>
      <div class="algo-purpose">Stateful hash-based schemes for specialised hardware and governmental contexts. State management complexity limits general use — requiring careful operational governance.</div>
      <div class="algo-42001">
        <strong>ISO 42001 Governance Touch</strong>
        Clause 8.1: Operational controls for state management of stateful signature schemes. Clause 8.2: Risk assess AI components managing signing state to prevent re-use vulnerabilities.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="algo-card">
      <div class="algo-fips">Hybrid Transition · IETF</div>
      <div class="algo-name">PQ/T Hybrids</div>
      <div class="algo-basis">PQC + Classical Combined<br>(X25519 + ML-KEM, etc.)</div>
