  <div class="warning-banner">
    <div class="warning-icon">⚡</div>
    <div class="warning-content">
      <div class="warning-title">The Non-Determinism Problem — Honest Assessment</div>
      <p>ISO 42001 does <strong>not</strong> use the terms "non-deterministic," "stochastic," or "quantum" in
      its normative text. The explicit accounting for non-determinism in a quantum-vulnerable environment
      must be <strong>constructed by the implementer</strong> through: (1) quantifying quantum adversary threat
      models in Clause 4.1 environmental analysis; (2) defining variance-aware risk criteria in Clause 6.1.2;
      (3) populating impact assessments with quantum-threat intelligence (NIST SP 800-208, ETSI GR QSC 006,
      ENISA PQC guidelines). The standard provides the scaffold. The domain expertise — your responsibility.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

