      <div class="control-name">Stakeholder Engagement</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Engage cryptographic operations teams, CISO, and end-users in AI system impact assessments. PQC context: customer notification for AI-driven migration recommendation changes.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4 style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent-gold); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 22px 0 14px;">DOMAIN: DATA GOVERNANCE (ANNEX A.6)</h4>
  <div class="control-grid">
    <div class="control-item gold">
      <div class="control-ref">A.6.1</div>
      <div class="control-name">Data Quality</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Training data quality requirements for ML models in cryptographic pipelines. Entropy samples, historical key usage patterns, and cipher suite telemetry must meet documented quality criteria.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item gold">
      <div class="control-ref">A.6.2</div>
      <div class="control-name">Data Provenance</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Cryptographic data provenance chain: who collected entropy samples, what TRNG hardware, when, under what conditions. Critical for NIST SP 800-90B compliance of AI entropy validators.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item gold">
      <div class="control-ref">A.6.4</div>
      <div class="control-name">Data Protection</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Protection of data used in AI model training and inference — particularly key usage telemetry and cryptographic operation logs that may reveal sensitive patterns if extracted.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4 style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent-violet); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 22px 0 14px;">DOMAIN: MODEL LIFECYCLE (ANNEX A.7 + A.9)</h4>
  <div class="control-grid">
    <div class="control-item violet">
      <div class="control-ref">A.7.1</div>
      <div class="control-name">Decision Audit Trails</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Every AI-assisted cryptographic decision must be logged: entropy accept/reject, anomaly classification, key rotation recommendations. Anti-repudiation requirement for PQC migration advisors.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item violet">
      <div class="control-ref">A.7.2</div>
      <div class="control-name">AI Model Transparency</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Explainability requirements for AI decisions in security-critical paths. A classifier flagging a TLS session as anomalous must produce human-interpretable reasoning for human-in-the-loop review.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item violet">
      <div class="control-ref">A.9.1</div>
      <div class="control-name">Secure Development</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Anti-tampering controls for AI model development environments. PQC context: isolated development environments for ML-KEM parameter selection models, supply chain validation of ML frameworks.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item violet">
      <div class="control-ref">A.9.3</div>
      <div class="control-name">Model Testing &amp; Validation</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Pre-deployment testing of AI models under adversarial conditions. For PQC vendors: test entropy validators against known-bad QRNG outputs and adversarially crafted entropy streams.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4 style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent-green); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 22px 0 14px;">DOMAIN: OPERATIONS &amp; THIRD PARTIES (ANNEX A.10)</h4>
  <div class="control-grid">
    <div class="control-item green">
      <div class="control-ref">A.10.3</div>
      <div class="control-name">Availability &amp; Resilience</div>
      <div class="control-desc">AI availability guarantees for cryptographic operations. Entropy validation downtime halts key generation. Anomaly detector outages create blind spots. Define and enforce SLAs for AI components.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item green">
      <div class="control-ref">A.10.5</div>
      <div class="control-name">Incident Response</div>
      <div class="control-desc">AI-specific incident response for cryptographic failures: what happens when the entropy validator produces systematic false rejections? Escalation path and rollback procedures must be documented.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="control-item green">
      <div class="control-ref">A.10.6</div>
      <div class="control-name">Third-Party AI Governance</div>
      <div class="control-desc">Audit requirements for upstream AI components: cloud KMS AI features, HSM vendor firmware AI, entropy-as-a-service ML components. Extends ISO 27001 supplier management into AI-specific risk.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
