  <div class="callout">
    <div class="callout-label">📌 Key Limitation to Disclose</div>
    <p>ISO 42001 implementation requires <strong>significant domain expertise to populate meaningfully</strong>.
    The standard's threat-agnostic design means that a generic AIMS implementation will not address quantum
    adversary risks unless the implementer explicitly introduces PQC threat intelligence (NIST SP 800-208,
    ETSI GR QSC 006, ENISA PQC guidelines) into the Clause 4.1 environmental analysis and Clause 6.1.2
    risk criteria. Certification bodies conducting ISO 42001 audits for PQC vendors should include
    cryptographic security subject matter expertise in the audit team — a capability that remains rare
    as of 2026, with the AI audit market described by BSI as potentially becoming "the wild west."</p>
